translationBlock.key: Returns the value of a file at compile time only. Unlike read, this runs and is fully resolved at compile time. This is useful for optimization reasons, if you have a file that is unchanging, this can be used instead of read(), to prevent a runtime hit each time the code is executed. Otherwise, this method is equivalent to read(). The path must be fully resolved at compile time.
